This paper deals with the generation of quadrilateral meshes, which is a topic in computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of Riemannian metrics and the Gauss-Bonnet condition suggests a connection to differential geometry (cs.GR) and geometric topology (cs.GT). The mention of holonomy groups and parallel translation suggests a connection to differential geometry (cs.DG). Finally, the use of discrete Ricci flow and conformal structure deformation suggests a connection to computational geometry and topology (cs.SG).
